y, but I'm thinking cglib ReflectUtils might help.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Analyzing JaCoCo instrumentation**\\n\\nI’m thinking about how class bytes loaded at runtime from resources aren't instrumented by JaCoCo, although dynamic access tracing might be possible. So, coverage could still be questionable. If JaCoCo instruments classes upon loading, it would typically instrument all classes unless specifically excluded, which seems likely. However, what about the source context? If the class name remains the same, it might still produce a synthetic exclusion at line 31, which I need to keep in mind.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_cJeKhMJulfEp36lfFMxaw9VF|fc_09f16580a170f3c20169fb8975f37c81a18a3a7082fc0b0e9b", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "if [ -f tests/src/cglib/cglib-nodep/2.2.2/test-results-native/test/TEST-cglib.cglib_nodep.BeanCopierTest.xml ]; then cat tests/src/cglib/cglib-nodep/2.2.2/test-results-native/test/TEST-cglib.cglib_nodep.BeanCopierTest.xml; fi", "timeout": 1}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 2111, "output": 3143, "cacheRead": 40960, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 46214, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1778092357853, "responseId": "resp_09f16580a170f3c20169fb8947600481a1a5b3030d5caf4fd5"}}
