[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Exploring classloading issues**\n\nI'm considering whether a fresh classloader will help avoid the `class$net...` field from being set, but I realize the original static initialization already used that field. With MethodHandle, class$ is called independently, which isn't a better solution after all. However, I think it’s still valuable to add isolated initialization because the execution from `<clinit>` might be recognized differently when called from a public API. Next, I need to get the URL of the cglib code.\n\n**Evaluating class loading issues**\n\nI’m considering potential failures during static initialization, particularly if KeyFactory.create fails, leading to an ExceptionInInitializerError. I’d like to test this, but I want to avoid any failures if possible. I wonder if catching Throwable would be adequate for JVM behaviors. If it fails due to linkage issues, that complicates things. I could catch the ExceptionInInitializerError after that line, but I need to be cautious. It’s tricky with package-private interfaces and class load mechanisms in play, but I'm thinking cglib ReflectUtils might help.\n\n**Analyzing JaCoCo instrumentation**\n\nI’m thinking about how class bytes loaded at runtime from resources aren't instrumented by JaCoCo, although dynamic access tracing might be possible. So, coverage could still be questionable. If JaCoCo instruments classes upon loading, it would typically instrument all classes unless specifically excluded, which seems likely. However, what about the source context? If the class name remains the same, it might still produce a synthetic exclusion at line 31, which I need to keep in mind.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_09f16580a170f3c20169fb89483adc81a1928f8c77fe6406a6\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABp-4l1kN0FtF-MR0Rg4aiP7cI-AS2ZkXo7VQFdxUhra0iq2xktecfFbOTBDoydlP6j6iOm_z9GdhM884J75aRQQ4giy