[recv] {"type": "message_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Considering static initialization**\n\nI’m thinking about how static initialization can be triggered through public inheritance without involving direct reflection. Keeping MethodHandle might be accepted, but could it help reduce direct reflection? I really need to stay focused and avoid tests leading to native failures. If a subclass instantiates, it might trigger KeyFactory.create, which could invoke static initializer code generation. Also, BeanCopier's static initialization calls KeyFactory.create, which could potentially lead to issues in native environments.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_09f16580a170f3c20169fb897ded5481a1a831583a5a941981\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABp-4miWY-dqNT32YFb3R4FDCLmHUWIcF-WL_13MARMLwcC5iSxyCYGwIPmJ8m8G8B0wThH3Q1KI4AoXzNFFn9O2Kfbpm_d4-MG3YefeGIWZDmZoSO_zRuhUAHVm0cTD3qhnT3nM0vPPM8vIykd9mGiiq3DaEdzwTlwCTLe_q64RNFepPZTQWbw5meYhrpSq-ftkPiR_oLCm43Thb2Q9vVJUIbIHY8WEyoo6K0FJtOUYL9qVjO-bCQYrwR9yPPCdpRrEZYKQTXaSwBkEWBoxN26QqhQDOaLp2vpAXbf7jBpGeo94307xF0KAwcCRFZbbqC4xQ9GECWYzuC855q_M29pyZm1Ns3e5fXJtr_BtD9I7FE9_KS97aAf1aIeDV-VTFUd9SnR2723PrI3V7Pwc-MEBqVzeommgr1hyEDUv0ax-B4ZbTcTDOKW8ko2Y1KuC08bFhoNh0homSDYlidaQsgZlVKXolHm8yJU5DBq0HZaBIus5jXhX63Q_9EFjUhpWWeoTeRWZOxtgm5yvx1V7RYSMtmC9F4WeUWGzz045dFv5EcFrhZASJ1d5ZnUMKuCnbJzDgDGTtIAyVy0jxvrUjQI-Zq4Aal_oAB5RGZe4chZJ9HKlJwm9ezgO1QRwXq6ahJoEYgsg5ZarOXIhzo_6fP1FNky1eMB7SjmOvj8W_CZjstSDfhbk6AfLiOWvm0gaO2cU-u913yBzAzn9Lb-h-syaNKnpvpax51A9jGyBoSuLp0dnxqyX36dQEpfQ9-GdbScqQpgqg6UaQoyYaOjNpftfX9bTspjb1vrzQZ2syFg3gLvHLpekEylh1BnbaMKuR86bu_-lIHKUANtbHudB4J8ypISIE6FeNHk_OphkCyvliTS6YK_UEzrw774w5ccbvOFv3Vkj68RyXm-35faQ_zhn3BFzy9roQ24i4EuBAu61XUH68qGVS6eNyYz8wcaproi-vCUZkjL4kTlncAmh6cHbqbtZTQIyB9VcBVSxpP0rQozra0QANK5Y4v7zhaZNZY-6QsSZabHTbSwCS8M03zQrCyn7byTZqIdxDtv-Q3cHsFKyOhuEnguUDqTdy9U8WOLR_kLhALrJl6Hn4h8UE71Id_zLVlxjt1Q6Jqe9TcB0S8b1M-frC-X6Dv2XCvDu3ZK1qovFzcFv_TnplPE901o